  "id": "c82cce8f-6abb-527e-96c1-3c5d50db3757",
  "slug": "beef-pochero",
  "name": "Beef Pochero Recipe",
  "recipe_type": "dessert",
  "brief_description": "Beef Pochero is a Filipino Stew similar to that of \"Beef Nilaga\". This dish is complimented by the sweetness of the saba banana, and a unique sour blend is brought-in by the tomato sauce. A very enticing dish that is worth craving for; beef pochero brings out the delightful taste of our Spanish influ",
  "cuisine": null,
  "instructions": [
    {
      "position": 1,
      "text": "Heat oil in the pot and fry the banana until color turns golden brown. Once done, set the bananas aside"
    },
    {
      "position": 2,
      "text": "Put the chorizo in the same pot and fry each side until it browns. Remove and then set aside."
    },
    {
      "position": 3,
      "text": "Uisng the remaining oil (add more if needed), saut\u00e9 the garlic, onion, and tomato"
    },
    {
      "position": 4,
      "text": "Add the beef once the onion and tomato softens. Continue sauteeing until the exterior the beef turns light brown."
    },
    {
      "position": 5,
      "text": "Add fish sauce, tomato sauce, and whole pepper corn. Stir."
    },
    {
      "position": 6,
      "text": "Pour the water. Let it boil. Cover the pot and simmer until the meat gets tender. (You can also use a pressure cooker to tenderize the meat faster)"
    },
    {
      "position": 7,
      "text": "Add the fried chorizo back into the pot along with the fried bananas. Also add the potato and garbanzos. Simmer for minutes"
    },
    {
      "position": 8,
      "text": "Add the cabbage, long green beans and continue cooking for 5 minutes"
    },
    {
      "position": 9,
      "text": "Add the bok choy. Turn off the heat. Cover the pot for 5 minutes (the residual heat will completely cook the bok choy)."
    },
    {
      "position": 10,
      "text": "Transfer to a serving bowl. Serve hot. Share and Enjoy!"
    }
  ],
  "servings": 6,
  "cooking_time_minutes": 60,
  "preparation_time_minutes": 12,
  "rest_time_minutes": null,
